OSOGBO – Governor Adegboyega Oyetola, has charged local government chairmen in Osun state to utilise their position to promote the interest of the people. He gave the charge while addressing the forum of local government chairmen who visited him in his office recently. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network The governor,who reminded the visiting chairmen that they would render account of their stewardship to the electorate, also urged them to utilize the number of days at their disposal. He restated his resolve to continue to support and provide an enabling environment for the local government helmsmen. The state chairman, Association of Local Governments of Nigeria (ALGON), Hon. Samuel Idowu Abiodun appreciated the governor for his fatherly advice which he described as timely.